In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 24, 2016, as a National Day of Thanksgiving. He reflects on the history of Thanksgiving, highlighting the Pilgrims who sought refuge in America and were helped by the indigenous Wampanoag people. He emphasizes the importance of unity and gratitude, as well as the need to give back to the community. President Obama encourages Americans to come together on this day, express appreciation, and share their blessings with others.